      "id": "mnswhs2w",
      "questionNumber": 6,
      "questionText": "<p>Given below are two statements :</p>\n<p><b>Statement I :</b> On the basis of inductive effect, the order of stability of alkyl carbanions is $\\mathrm{CH}_3{ }^{-}>\\mathrm{CH}_3-\\mathrm{CH}_2{ }^{-}>\\left(\\mathrm{CH}_3\\right)_2 \\mathrm{CH}^{-}>\\left(\\mathrm{CH}_3\\right)_3 \\mathrm{C}^{-}$.</p>\n<p><b>Statement II :</b> Allyl and benzyl carbanions are more stabilised by inductive effect and not by resonance effect.</p>\n<p>In the light of the above statements, choose the correct answer from the options given below :</p>\n",
      "options": [
        "<p>Both Statement I and Statement II are correct</p>\n",
        "<p>Both Statement I and Statement II are incorrect</p>\n",
        "<p>Statement I is correct but Statement II is incorrect</p>\n",
        "<p>Statement I is incorrect but Statement II is correct</p>"
      ],
      "correctOption": 2,
      "correctAnswer": null,
      "questionType": "MCQ",
      "marks": 4,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "subject": "Chemistry",
      "topic": "stability-of-intermediate",
      "difficulty": "Easy",
      "solution": "<p><b>Statement-I</b></p>\n<p>$\\mathrm{CH}_3{ }^{-}&gt;\\mathrm{CH}_3-\\mathrm{CH}_2{ }^{-}&gt;\\left(\\mathrm{CH}_3\\right)_2 \\mathrm{CH}^{-}&gt;\\left(\\mathrm{CH}_3\\right)_3 \\mathrm{C}^{-}$</p>\n<p>It is correct order of anion stability and it is based on inductive effect.</p>\n<p><b>Statement-II</b></p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1mp06mywb/93d20649-04d2-4b6c-bf34-1ed0c1d2c0b6/c59acfb0-4ca8-11f1-9864-53d65aa0ef81/file-6y3zli1mp06mywc.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1mp06mywb/93d20649-04d2-4b6c-bf34-1ed0c1d2c0b6/c59acfb0-4ca8-11f1-9864-53d65aa0ef81/file-6y3zli1mp06mywc.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"JEE Main 2026 (Online) 5th April Morning Shift Chemistry - Basics of Organic Chemistry Question 5 English Explanation\"></p>\n<p>Both are stabilised by resonance</p>\n<p>Statement-I : Correct</p>\n<p>Statement-II : Incorrect</p>",
      "section": "A",
      "instruction": "",
      "examSource": "jee-main"
    },
